{{Cleanup FJC Bio}}
'''Solomon Blatt Jr.''' (born 1921) is a [[United States federal judge]].

Blatt was born in [[Sumter, South Carolina]]. He received a [[A.B.]] from [[University of South Carolina]] in 1941. He received a [[LL.B.]] from [[University of South Carolina Law Center]] in 1946. He was in the [[United States Navy]] from 1942 to 1946. He was in private practice of law in [[Barnwell, South Carolina]] from 1946 to 1971. 

Blatt was a federal judge to the [[United States District Court for the District of South Carolina]]. Blatt was nominated by President [[Richard M. Nixon]] on May 18, 1971, to a seat vacated by [[Donald Stuart Russell]]. He was confirmed by the [[United States Senate]] on May 26, 1971, and received commission on May 28, 1971. Served as chief judge, 1986-1990. Assumed [[senior status]] on May 7, 1990. 

